data.message: I feel so honored to be the first comment. All of my hardwork and dedication has paid off. Getting the top comment has been a dream of mine for many years, and I would like to thank those who have helped me along the way. Next I would like to thank my parents, for birthing me. I want to thank my fake cat Belle, for always being there for me. I also want to thank President Bush for allowing me to realize that if a mentally challenged child can be president, I can be 1st comment... This is a special moment in my life and I would like to thank any of my unmentioned friends and family that have helped me along the way. This moment will be an experience that I will never forget. And last but not least I would like to thank all of the millions of people/fans out there that took time out of their day to celebrate this momentous achievement with me. I cannot stress how much of a big deal this is. I have been trying to be the first comment on a post for years, but that has not been possible until this amazing day. Hopefully my good luck will continue, but this is undoubtedly a rare occasion. If you asked me how I did this, I would say, you can achieve anything you set your mind to. To all the kids out there reading this, I would like to tell them to follow their dreams, the sky is the limit. Being the top comment is amazing, thank you everyone

I've been in love with Nike Shox for about 6years, I get a new pair about every 6 months, and both my children have a few pairs as well as husband, and I have foster children ,and I buy them shox as well. I was saddened this last time, I bought a pair fo r$149.00, they were defective, I sent them in, they approved, (i wasn't worried because it was seriously obvious) It had a piece of hard rubber/plastic poking me in my foot which caused me to actually have part of my nail removed because of it, I didn't ask for anything other than a replacement pair. I had to pay $15.00 to shipmy shoes to Nike, and then the turnaround was amazing, however, they gave me $110.00. I invested over 165.00 for the shoes themselves, and they didn't refund the full price, and I can only use the voucher online, they don't have Shox NZ even similar to the colors or type that I would wear under $150.00. I wear the shox NZ and have for 6years. I have medical conditions and that is the only pair that doesn't make my my feet swell when I wear them, So not only am I now stuck paying $40.00 extra to get a pair of SHox NZ that I would wear, I don't have my originial shox that I LOVE now they are telling me I have to pay an additional $12.00 in shipping. SO now I am out $1000.00 in Medical because of a shoe, $165.00 for my original shoe, and shipping to get it back to your company, and have to pay additional $40.00 in  charges to get a replacement pair, PLUS shipping AGAIN to get it to me,HOw in the WORLD is that REPLACING MY SHOES. The total expenses this has caused me is $1217.00. All this after I invest in a new pair every 6 months for my entire family, and your telling me you wont at the VERY LEAST cover the shipping to get me a replacement pair. ARe you serious right now? I think if your "replacing" my shoes as I was told by the gentlemen on the phone when I originally called, You should either at least cover the shipping to get me a new pair, or make my voucher $150.00, which is the price it would cost me to replace my shox NZ, or give me the option to at least go to an outlet store that sells shox so that I can pick a pair that I actually like, instead of giving me a voucher than can only be used at Nike.com. I really would hate to have to stop buying shoes that I have more than invested over $1800.00 a YEAR for 6years. OVER 10K in Nikes. And you can't "REPLACE" MY SHOES, OR PAY THE SHIPPING BECAUSE THEY ARE SHOX NZ AND THEY ARE ID. Customer service is huge to me, and when I feel like I have been disrespected or brushed off like I don't matter, I don't take that lightly obviously, and when I called customer service yesterday I was told to bad. ARE YOU KIDDING ME? I think Nike needs to make this right, All I want is A REplacement pair, I don't think I am asking for anything insane here, It takes $150.00 to replace my shox, then you should be more than happy to replace them at that cost, or LOWER your prices online. I can't replace my shoes, or my toenail for $110.00. Make it right Nike that's all I am asking. Or at the LEAST LEAST LEAST cover the shipping for me to order another pair online.
